SIMPLE: suppliant
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suppliant
<hw>Sup"pli*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., p. pr. of
<ets>supplier</ets> to entreat, L. <ets>supplicare</ets>. See
<er>Supplicate</er>, and cf. <er>Supplicant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Asking earnestly and submissively; entreating; beseeching;
supplicating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rich grow <qex>suppliant</qex>, and the poor grow proud.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Manifesting entreaty; expressive of
supplication.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To bow and sue for grace⟦br⟧
With <qex>suppliant</qex> knee.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Entreating; beseeching; suing; begging;
supplicating; imploring.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sup"pli*ant*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sup"pli*ant*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suppliant</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suppliant
<hw>Sup"pli*ant</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who supplicates; a humble
petitioner; one who entreats submissively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hear thy <qex>suppliant's</qex> prayer.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supplicancy</ent>⟦br⟧
